## Quick Reference Table

| Language   | Library              | Annotation/Decorator          |
|------------|----------------------|-------------------------------|
| Go         | `encoding/json`      | `` `json:"name"` ``           |
| Python     | Pydantic             | `Field(alias="name")`         |
| TypeScript | class-transformer    | `@Expose({ name: "name" })`   |
| C#         | System.Text.Json     | `[JsonPropertyName("name")]`  |
| C#         | Newtonsoft           | `[JsonProperty("name")]`      |
| Java       | Jackson              | `@JsonProperty("name")`       |

---

> **Key Use Cases:**
> - Map `snake_case` JSON ↔ `camelCase` code
> - Ignore sensitive fields (`password`, `token`)
> - Support legacy API field names
